sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant CH as User Channel
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant LG as LangGraph Runtime
    participant IA as Intake Agent Node
    participant KA as Knowledge Agent (RAG)
    participant WF as Workflow Agent (MCP)
    participant EA as Escalation Agent
    participant MC as MCP Tools
    participant IT as ITSM System
    participant HU as Human IT

    U->>CH: Sends request (e.g., "Reset my VPN password" or "VPN keeps dropping")
    CH->>GW: Normalize + forward message
    GW->>LG: Deliver ChatEvent + session context
    LG->>IA: Determine intent, entities, severity
    IA-->>LG: intent/request_type, system, confidence, severity

    alt [Informational Query]
        LG->>KA: Perform RAG search via PDFs + Chroma
        KA->>KA: Retrieve chunks, build context prompt
        KA-->>LG: Provide answer + citations
        LG-->>CH: Final Answer (no automation)
    end

    alt [Action or Incident]
        LG->>WF: Execute workflow (e.g., reset password, get logs)
        WF->>MC: Call tools (idp.reset_password, logs.get_recent)
        MC-->>WF: Tool responses (success/failure)
        WF-->>LG: Workflow completed or partially failed

        alt [Workflow Succeeded]
            LG-->>CH: Output completion summary + ticket ID
        end

        Note over LG,EA: [Requires Escalation]
        LG->>EA: Summarize issue + diagnostics
        EA->>IT: itsm.create_incident()
        IT->>IT: Create incident with context
        IT-->>EA: Ticket ID
        EA-->>LG: Escalation summary
        LG-->>CH: "Escalated to IT: Ticket #INC-..."
        IT->>HU: Assign incident + AI context
    end
